The paper deals with algorithms for computing subgraphs of a given graph that satisfy certain constraints, such as Steiner trees and spanners. This falls under the category of graph algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and numerical experiments, which are relevant to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper mentions the use of linear programming and optimization, which is related to game theory (cs.GT).
